Description: Fragment of flattened handle of an Ephesian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff-brown; much small mica. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Diodoros. Trimmed. Nikandros group. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.110,11.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1704)
